-- int_deduped_returns.sql
```sql
-- Deduplicate returns to one approved return per item
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        return_id,
        item_id,
        return_date,
        reason,
        status,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY item_id
            ORDER BY return_date DESC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_returns') }}
    WHERE status = 'approved'
)
SELECT
    return_id,
    item_id,
    return_date,
    reason,
    status
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

-- fct_return_rates_by_category.sql
```sql
-- Calculate product return rates by category
SELECT
    COALESCE(c.name, '(unknown)') AS category_name,
    SUM(oi.quantity) AS total_items_sold,
    SUM(CASE WHEN r.item_id IS NOT NULL THEN oi.quantity ELSE 0 END) AS total_items_returned,
    SUM(CASE WHEN r.item_id IS NOT NULL THEN oi.quantity ELSE 0 END) / CAST(SUM(oi.quantity) AS DECIMAL(10,2)) AS return_rate
FROM {{ ref('stg_order_items') }} oi
LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_products') }} p
    ON p.product_id = oi.product_id
LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_categories') }} c
    ON c.category_id = p.category_id
LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_deduped_returns') }} r
    ON r.item_id = oi.item_id
GROUP BY
    COALESCE(c.name, '(unknown)')
